		<content:encoded><![CDATA[Since naming <a href="http://troyandgay.com/blog/2009/04/25/hudsons-8-months-old/">Hudson</a>, "Hudson" has popped up a lot that we've noticed. Our contact at our bank has a last name of Hudson, the actress Jennifer Hudson had a family tragedy and she sang at the Steelers Super Bowl, a plane miraculously landed in the Hudson in New York, and <em>two</em> restaurants have opened in Seattle recently: <a href="http://washingtonbeerblog.com/2009/04/14/the-hudson-new-american-public-house-open-for-business/">Hudson Public House</a> and <a href="http://hudsonseattle.com/">Hudson Restaurant</a>. Ironically, we picked the name because our other top choice was too trendy.

<strong>Update</strong>: Another reference today to Hudson in NYT <a href="http://cityroom.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/04/27/air-force-one-backup-rattles-new-york-nerve/">photo and article</a>.]]></content:encoded>
